Musalia Mudavadi has dramatically jumped to being the preferred running mate for William Ruto in the August 9 presidential election, according to a February opinion poll by Radio Africa Group. The poll found that 33.9 per cent of respondents said Mudavadi would be the best running mate for Ruto while 19.6 per cent picked Mathira MP Rigathi Gachagua. Then 11.5 per cent said Martha Karua would be his best running mate followed by Kalonzo Musyoka with 5.2 per cent.